explicitly. See [session.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/session.rs:261), [session.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/session.rs:285), [serialize.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/serialize.rs:548), [materialize.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/materialize.rs:189).\n\nLeave alone: the core `MetadataKeyMatch::{Exact, Prefix}` shape is generic enough; the agentlog naming is confined to tests. `Prefix` being raw string-prefix matching is acceptable as long as callers choose delimiter-aware prefixes like `foo:`. See [types.rs](/Users/kiril/src/git-meta/crates/git-meta-lib/src/types.rs:342).\n\nLeave alone: `Session::{serialize_scope, materialize_scope}` as operations seem like valid GitMeta plumbing primitives, not agentlog-specific APIs. The main issue is making their boundary contract explicit and trimming/refining public ref helpers, not renaming them to agentlog concepts.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T17:56:04.171Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}